    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/391f5e4ae43b090c22f3abfa6bf8fa75?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
                "account_id": 9609012,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 7134058,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7134058/vadim",
                "reputation": 4130,
                "display_name": "Vadim"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1479335259,
            "creation_date": 1479335259,
            "body": "<p><strong>AJNeufeld:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>\"but you must still specify the dependencies in the child modules\"<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>It is correct only if dependency is in &lt;dependencyManagement&gt;. Just try to set &lt;dependency&gt; in parent &lt;dependencies&gt; and do not set same dependency in child at all.<\/p>\n\n<p>Parent POM:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;project&gt;\n ...\n &lt;dependencies&gt;\n   ...\n   &lt;dependency&gt;\n     &lt;groupId&gt;junit&lt;/groupId&gt;\n     &lt;artifactId&gt;junit&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n     &lt;version&gt;4.12&lt;/version&gt;\n     &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;\n   &lt;/dependency&gt;\n   ...\n &lt;dependencies&gt;\n ...\n&lt;/project&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Child POM:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;project&gt;\n  ...\n  &lt;!-- no junit dependency defined at all --&gt;\n  ...\n&lt;/project&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 40643501,
            "question_id": 40642567
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1e2d5067f52318f0ed4db9eca0b2cda1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 4542619,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 3690024,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3690024/ajneufeld",
                "reputation": 8747,
                "display_name": "AJNeufeld"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1479333511,
            "creation_date": 1479333511,
            "body": "<p>You can configure dependencies in the parent, but you must still specify the dependencies in the child modules.\nThis allows you to specify the version <strong>once<\/strong> in the parent POM, and have all child modules use that version.\nEach child module must still list its dependencies, though.<\/p>\n\n<p>Parent POM:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;project&gt;\n   ...\n   &lt;dependencyManagement&gt;\n       &lt;dependencies&gt;\n           &lt;dependency&gt;\n              &lt;groupId&gt;junit&lt;/groupId&gt;\n              &lt;artifactId&gt;junit&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n              &lt;version&gt;4.12&lt;/version&gt;\n              &lt;scope&gt;test&lt;/scope&gt;\n          &lt;/dependency&gt;\n         ...\n       &lt;dependencies&gt;\n   &lt;/dependencyManagement&gt;\n   ...\n&lt;/project&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Child POMs:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;project&gt;\n   ...\n   &lt;dependencies&gt;\n       &lt;dependency&gt;\n           &lt;groupId&gt;junit&lt;/groupId&gt;\n           &lt;artifactId&gt;junit&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n       &lt;/dependency&gt;\n      ...\n   &lt;/dependencies&gt;\n   ...\n&lt;/project&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 40643119,
            "question_id": 40642567
        }
    ],
